    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Chargé in Cuba (
                        Wright
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d770</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">770</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-22T18:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-22T18:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-22T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-22T18:00:00-05:00" n="770" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d770">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.61351/6–2245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-22T19:00:00-04:00">June 22, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>424. This morning at final meeting with Cuban Sugar Commission,<note n="83" xml:id="d770fn83">Meetings of the United States and Cuban Commissions began
                        in Habana on June 10.</note> they stated that because of 1946 crop
                    uncertainty and our offer for only one crop, they could not get industry’s
                    support to continue negotiations until October. They, however, repeatedly
                    assured that U.S. would get Cuba’s 1946 production.</p>
                <pb facs="0950" n="936" xml:id="pg_936"/>
                <p>A joint press release was issued stating our offer to purchase one crop at 3.45
                    and that discussions would be resumed with Cubans before October 15.</p>
                <p>Wilson and Rowe left for Washington this afternoon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
